HEADWORD: Gas-burner
<hw>Gas"-burn`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The jet piece of
a gas fixture where the gas is burned as it escapes from one or more
minute orifices.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

